cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.NA 

The paper deals with coding theory and the Golomb-Welch conjecture, which is a problem in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of an invariant connected to abelian groups, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses algebraic structures and graph theory, which are covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) respectively. Finally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which are covered in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
